<subSubSection id="24CB1080FFA1FFFCFAB2A8C082A7FDD8" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="6C6E430BFFA1FFFCFAB2A8C0821DFE6D" blockId="21.[151,1437,1714,2029]" lastBlockId="22.[151,1437,151,393]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA1FFFFFAB2A8C0815EF82C" bold="true" box="[199,315,1966,1992]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Remarks.</emphasis>
The coordinates of previous records from the coast of 
<collectingRegion id="AE158DE9FFA1FFFFF9BFA8C0845AF82C" box="[970,1087,1966,1992]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
refers to 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFA1FFFFFEC3A8C0850DF82C" baseAuthorityName="S I Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[1206,1384,1966,1992]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Sergia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="robustus">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA1FFFFFEC3A8C0850DF82C" box="[1206,1384,1966,1992]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Sergia robustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and are 
<geoCoordinate id="09E525CCFFA1FFFFFAB6A8BC817FF808" box="[195,282,2002,2028]" degrees="24" direction="south" minutes="16" orientation="latitude" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" precision="925" value="-24.266666">24°16’S</geoCoordinate>
/ 
<geoCoordinate id="09E525CCFFA1FFFFFB56A8BC81E8F808" box="[291,397,2002,2028]" degrees="44" direction="west" minutes="00" orientation="longitude" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" precision="925" value="-44.0">44°00’W</geoCoordinate>
, which is close to Ubatuba (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFA1FFFFF8ADA8BC83E2F809" author="D'Incao, F." box="[728,903,2002,2029]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" refId="ref59841" refString="D'Incao, F. (1995 a) Taxonomia, padroes distribucionais e ecologicos dos Dendrobranchiata (Crustacea: Decapoda) do Brasil e Atlantico Ocidental. PhD Thesis, Universidade Federal do Parana, Brasil, 365 pp." type="book" year="1995">D’Incao 1995a</bibRefCitation>
). This species was first described as 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFA1FFFCFF41A8BC81FDFF55" authority="(Smith, 1882)" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1882" class="Malacostraca" family="Sergestidae" genus="Sergestes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="23" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robustus">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA1FFFCFF41A8BC8093FF55" italics="true" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Sergestes robustus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFA2FFFCFB71AFF981F4FF55" author="Smith, S. I." box="[260,401,151,177]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="1 - 108" refId="ref78912" refString="Smith, S. I. (1882) Reports on the results of dredging under the supervision of Alexander Agassiz, on the east coast of the United States during the summer of 1880, by the U. S. Coast Survey Steamer &quot; Blake &quot;, Commander J. R. Bartlett, U. S. N., Commanding. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology at Harvard College, 10 (1), 1 - 108." type="journal article" year="1882">Smith, 1882</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and reclassified as 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFA2FFFCF807AFF98370FF55" baseAuthorityName="S.I.Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[626,789,151,177]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Sergia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="robusta">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA2FFFCF807AFF98370FF55" box="[626,789,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Sergia robusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
afterward (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFA2FFFCF9E4AFF98407FF55" author="Vereshchaka, A. L." box="[913,1122,151,177]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="69 - 207" refId="ref81707" refString="Vereshchaka, A. L. (2000) Revision of the genus Sergia (Decapoda: Dendrobranchiata: Sergestidae): taxonomy and distribution. Galathea Reports, 18, 69 - 207." type="journal article" year="2000">Vereshchaka 2000</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFA2FFFCFE19AFF985F4FF55" author="De Grave, S. &amp; Fransen, C. H. J. M." box="[1132,1425,151,177]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="195 - 589" refId="ref60882" refString="De Grave, S. &amp; Fransen, C. H. J. M. (2011) Carideorum catalogus: the recent species of the dendrobranchiate, stenopodidean, procarididean and caridean shrimps (Crustacea: Decapoda). Zoologische Mededelingen, 85 (9), 195 - 589." type="journal article" year="2011">De Grave &amp; Fransen 2011</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFA2FFFCFAE2AFD581D0FF31" author="Vereshchaka, A. L. &amp; Olesen, J. &amp; Lunina, A. A." box="[151,437,187,213]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="112057" refId="ref81810" refString="Vereshchaka, A. L., Olesen, J. &amp; Lunina, A. A. (2014) Global diversity and phylogeny of pelagic shrimps of the former genera Sergestes and Sergia (Crustacea, Dendrobranchiata, Sergestidae), with definition of eight new genera. PloS ONE, 9 (11), e 112057. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0112057" type="journal article" year="2014">
Vereshchaka 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA2FFFCFB5EAFD58106FF31" box="[299,355,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">et al.</emphasis>
(2014)
</bibRefCitation>
describes a new genus 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFA2FFFCF8CEAFD58566FF31" authority="Vereshchaka, Olesen &amp; Lunina, 2014" authorityName="Vereshchaka, Olesen &amp; Lunina" authorityYear="2014" box="[699,1283,187,213]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sergestidae" genus="Robustosergia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA2FFFCF8CEAFD58339FF31" box="[699,860,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Robustosergia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFA2FFFCF917AFD58566FF31" author="Vereshchaka, A. L. &amp; Olesen, J. &amp; Lunina, A. A." box="[866,1283,187,213]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="112057" refId="ref81810" refString="Vereshchaka, A. L., Olesen, J. &amp; Lunina, A. A. (2014) Global diversity and phylogeny of pelagic shrimps of the former genera Sergestes and Sergia (Crustacea, Dendrobranchiata, Sergestidae), with definition of eight new genera. PloS ONE, 9 (11), e 112057. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0112057" type="journal article" year="2014">Vereshchaka, Olesen &amp; Lunina, 2014</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
including the four species of 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFA2FFFCFB33AFB181DCFF1D" baseAuthorityName="S.I.Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[326,441,223,249]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Sergia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="robusta">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA2FFFCFB33AFB181DCFF1D" box="[326,441,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">S. robusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex (
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFA2FFFCF8FEAFB18298FF1D" baseAuthorityName="S.I.Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[651,765,223,249]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Sergia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="robusta">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA2FFFCF8FEAFB18298FF1D" box="[651,765,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">S. robusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFA2FFFCF979AFB18313FF1D" authorityName="Gordon" authorityYear="1939" baseAuthorityName="Gordon" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[780,886,223,249]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Sergia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="regalis">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA2FFFCF979AFB18313FF1D" box="[780,886,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">S. regalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFA2FFFCF9F0AFB1846AFF1C" baseAuthorityName="Burkenroad" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[901,1039,223,249]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Sergia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="extenuata">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA2FFFCF9F0AFB1846AFF1C" box="[901,1039,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">S. extenuata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFA2FFFCFE6BAFB184E1FF1C" authorityName="Vereshchaka" authorityYear="2000" box="[1054,1156,223,249]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Sergia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vityazi">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA2FFFCFE6BAFB184E1FF1C" box="[1054,1156,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">S. vityazi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). We did not collect this species, since it is known to occur at depths of 200 and 
<quantity id="AB29EEEEFFA2FFFCF97DAE6C8300FEF9" box="[776,869,258,285]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="m" value="5000.0">5,000 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFA2FFFCF906AE6D8445FEF9" author="D'Incao, F." box="[883,1056,258,285]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refId="ref59841" refString="D'Incao, F. (1995 a) Taxonomia, padroes distribucionais e ecologicos dos Dendrobranchiata (Crustacea: Decapoda) do Brasil e Atlantico Ocidental. PhD Thesis, Universidade Federal do Parana, Brasil, 365 pp." type="book" year="1995">D’Incao 1995a</bibRefCitation>
), predominantly between 600 and 
<quantity id="AB29EEEEFFA2FFFCFAE2AE498091FEA5" box="[151,244,295,321]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="m" value="1000.0">1,000 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFA2FFFCFB76AE4981A8FEA5" author="Timm, L. E. &amp; Isma, L. M. &amp; Johnston, M. W. &amp; Bracken-Grissom, H. D." box="[259,461,295,321]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="19" refId="ref80814" refString="Timm, L. E., Isma, L. M., Johnston, M. W. &amp; Bracken-Grissom, H. D. (2020) Comparative population genomics and biophysical modeling of shrimp migration in the Gulf of Mexico reveals current-mediated connectivity. Frontiers in Marine Science, 7, 19. https: // doi. org / 10.3389 / fmars. 2020.00019" type="journal article" year="2020">
Timm 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA2FFFCFB25AE4981ECFEA5" box="[336,393,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
); they are sampled with demersal and pelagic trawls (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFA2FFFCFE5FAE49856BFEA5" author="Cardoso, I. A. &amp; Falkenhaug, T. &amp; Fernandes, L. F. L." box="[1066,1294,295,321]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="47 - 56" refId="ref56070" refString="Cardoso, I. A., Falkenhaug, T. &amp; Fernandes, L. F. L. (2014) Comparison between the shrimp species richness (Caridea and Dendrobranchiata, Decapoda, Crustacea) of the south and north mid Atlantic ridge. Brazilian Journal of Oceanography, 62 (1), 47 - 56. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / s 1679 - 87592014060706201" type="journal article" year="2014">
Cardoso 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA2FFFCFEE4AE4984AFFEA5" box="[1169,1226,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
). We did not reach such depths or use such collecting gear. There is a COI sequence (JSDPX79-05 = 
<accessionNumber id="7382DEE8FFA2FFFCFEF8AE258564FE82" box="[1165,1281,331,358]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/JQ306179" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">JQ306179</accessionNumber>
) available on GenBank by 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFA2FFFCFB5EAE018211FE6D" author="Matzen da Silva, J. &amp; Creer, S. &amp; Santos, A. &amp; Costa, A. C. &amp; Cunha, M. R. &amp; Costa, F. O. &amp; Carvalho, G. R." box="[299,628,367,393]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="19449" refId="ref69088" refString="Matzen da Silva, J., Creer, S., Santos, A., Costa, A. C., Cunha, M. R., Costa, F. O. &amp; Carvalho, G. R. (2011) Systematic and evolutionary insights derived from mtDNA COI barcode diversity in the Decapoda (Crustacea: Malacostraca). PLoS ONE, 6 (5), e 19449. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0019449" type="journal article" year="2011">
Matzen da Silva 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA2FFFCFB9DAE01827CFE6D" box="[488,537,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">et al</emphasis>
. (2011)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6C6E430BFFA2FFFCFAE2AEB482F8FE10" blockId="22.[151,669,474,501]" box="[151,669,474,501]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
